<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>$this-&gt;assertResponseCode(200); currently gives (when in error): "Failed asserting response code "200""</p>

<p>I would propose changing it to something like: "Failed asserting that response code &lt;301&gt; matches expected &lt;200&gt;."</p>

<p>This way you can see what the actual error code was, and it's more in line with assertEquals().</p>

